# Project Context
This is "Vikara AI", an AI-native voice and interview scheduling agent. It acts as an autonomous HR orchestrator to eliminate timezone friction for global recruiting.

# Tech Stack & Standards
- Backend: Python (FastAPI)
- AI/LLMs: Groq, OpenAI, Retell AI SDK
- Tools: Google Calendar API (via google-api-python-client)
- Database: MongoDB (pymongo)

# Cursor AI Guidelines
- Always write strictly type-hinted Python code.
- Prefer async/await patterns for external API calls (LLMs, Calendar, WebSockets).
- Never hardcode API keys or credentials; always assume they will be loaded from a `.env` file.
- Maintain modular separation between the LLM reasoning layer (`llm.py`) and the external tool execution layer (`calendar_tools.py`).